 Then for
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\vec{x} & =\left(a,a\right)\\
\vec{y} & =\left(a,b\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

we denote where 
\begin_inset Formula $k\r\KK$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{c}_{0}=\left(\enc_{k}\left(a\right),\enc_{k}\left(a\right)\right),\vec{c}_{1}=\left(\enc_{k}\left(a\right),\enc_{k}\left(b\right)\right)$
